Date: Fri, 12 Apr 2013 15:33:11 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 0081/1074] ENGR00258733 WEIM-NOR: mtd: cfi_cmdset_0002: Do
 not release the mutex lock

The NOR(M29W256GL7AN6E) may suffers a write-buffer timeout during
the bonnie++/ubifs stress test. Micron has confirmed that it is
a silicon bug in the Nor.

This patch is just a workaround to fix this issue for this NOR.

With this patch, the read/write/erase will do in the synchronous way.

Signed-off-by: Huang Shijie <b32955@freescale.com>
[Original patch taken from git://git.freescale.com/imx/linux-2.6-imx.git]
Signed-off-by: Biyao Zhai <biyao.zhai@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/mtd/chips/cfi_cmdset_0002.c |    4 ----
 1 files changed, 0 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/mtd/chips/cfi_cmdset_0002.c b/drivers/mtd/chips/cfi_cmdset_0002.c
index 718244d..9aaebdb 100644
--- a/drivers/mtd/chips/cfi_cmdset_0002.c
+++ b/drivers/mtd/chips/cfi_cmdset_0002.c
@@ -1057,17 +1057,13 @@ static void __xipram xip_udelay(struct map_info *map, struct flchip *chip,
 
 #define UDELAY(map, chip, adr, usec)  \
 do {  \
-	mutex_unlock(&chip->mutex);  \
 	cfi_udelay(usec);  \
-	mutex_lock(&chip->mutex);  \
 } while (0)
 
 #define INVALIDATE_CACHE_UDELAY(map, chip, adr, len, usec)  \
 do {  \
-	mutex_unlock(&chip->mutex);  \
 	INVALIDATE_CACHED_RANGE(map, adr, len);  \
 	cfi_udelay(usec);  \
-	mutex_lock(&chip->mutex);  \
 } while (0)
 
 #endif
